Graduate from a residency program unique to the Netherlands (including a Master in International Health), preparing doctors to work in humanitarian aid/resource-low settings. I've been working in Ethiopia for almost 1,5 years now; first in Oromiya region, and now in AA. Previous working experience in Kenya, Tanzania and Zambia. text:
Hi everyone, I'm Selam and I probably stick out from you all in terms of skillset--I'm a mechanical engineer based in Cambridge, MA. Like a few others I'm also an MIT alumn and currently work in robotics research.

I know the focus here is to prevent the outbreak from happening, but I think looking ahead to strengthen the healthcare system may be valuable given the exponential nature of growth. There have been multiple efforts here in Massachusetts to do rapid manufacturing of respirators using 3D printers, and increase production of masks. Ethiopia already has textile manufacturing facilities that could be helpful for the masks, which are also preventative. I'd be happy to share more if/when it's needed.

Also have some experience in fundraising, project management, research, grant writing, and writing/advertising (English)
